title: Female Founders & VC in Healthcare
description: Come join a panel conversation with three female founders building companies in healthcare! We’ll dive into the challenges and breakthroughs of building and scaling healthcare startups, especially as a female founder — the highs, the lows, and everything in between. We'll share honest stories, practical learnings, and a chance to connect with other folks working at the intersection of healthcare and innovation. All folks welcome! Our panelists will be: Celina Qi, Co-Founder and COO at Camber; Nikita Singareddy, Co-Founder and CEO at Fortuna Health; Wendy Tsu, Co-Founder at Branch Care. Our moderator will be Lainy Painter, at Craft Ventures. Thank you to our partners at a16z and Goodwin Procter, and excited to see you all there!

title: ElevenLabs - Creating Incredible Enterprise Experiences with Voice AI
description: Join ElevenLabs for an evening at a Manhattan rooftop as we bring together industry leaders to discuss how AI agents are transforming the way businesses engage with their customers. We’ll kick things off with a fireside chat featuring industry experts who will share real-world insights on what they’ve built, the impact they’ve seen, and the challenges they’ve faced. Afterward, stick around for a cocktail hour with an open bar, hors d’oeuvres, and the chance to connect with other forward-thinking operators, builders, and customers. Spots are limited — we’d love to see you there.

title: Kindred x a16z: Travel, Reimagined
description: Join us for a special evening of connection, conversation, and community at Bogart House—a stunning venue with sweeping views of the New York skyline. We’re excited to host a fireside chat featuring Kindred co-founder and CEO, Justine Palefsky, in conversation with longtime Kindred member Bob Krinsky. Together, they’ll explore the spirit of Kindred, the power of trust in travel, and the community we’re building—followed by an open Q&A with guests. The evening will flow like this: 🎉 Welcome + Networking: Mingle and meet fellow Kindred members, friends of the community, and guests from Tech Week. 🔥 Fireside Chat: Settle in for a 45-minute conversation between Justine and Bob, with space for live questions from the audience. 🌆 Open Social: Stick around to enjoy live music, skyline views, and great company as the night unfolds. 🥂 Kindred will be providing appetizers for all guests, with drinks available for purchase at the bar. Whether you’re a longtime member or new to the Kindred community, we’d love for you to join us for what promises to be a memorable night of meaningful conversations, music, and new connections.

title: AI Builders x Reddit Games Happy Hour
description: Calling all AI Builders– build a game on Reddit! 🍔Food & 🍻Drinks + Views from 1WTC @ the Reddit Office. Note: Because of building security, please provide your first/last name and ensure you bring an ID that matches. If you're not RSVP'ed yourself you won't be able to get in! Developers can build games and social experiences on Reddit’s developer platform and earn up to $116k per app. We’re hosting a Happy Hour for AI builders to connect and learn about building games and social experiences on Reddit. Bring your laptop and use your favorite AI tools to code and launch an app. Get Reddit swag for deploying your first Reddit app. Agenda: 5PM - Check-in & Drinks; 6PM - Reddit Games Demo + Food; 7PM - Mini hackathon + Swag giveaway. Hosted by Reddit’s Developer Platform, Devvit. Join subreddit r/Devvit or discord. Learn more about Reddit Developer Funds: https://developers.reddit.com/docs/reddit_developer_funds.

title: IPO Journey in the Era of AI
description: This session brings CEOs, CFOs and leaders from rising venture capital-backed tech and GenAI companies into conversation with investors, legal specialists and banking professionals, culminating in an exclusive panel to share insights on emerging capital market trends, funding opportunities and the strategic steps required to scale from startup to public market success. What you can expect: 1. Insights on capital market trends and practical steps for navigating the IPO process; 2. A look at how generative AI can accelerate growth and influence funding decisions; 3. Essential legal, financial and operational considerations for scaling from private to public.

title: a16z Speedrun One Last Round
description: Join us for an informal mixer during NY Tech Week to meet the partners and operators behind a16z Speedrun—our early-stage startup program for founders. We’ll be hanging out, answering questions about the program, and giving you a sense of what it’s like to work with us. If you’ve been curious about Speedrun, this is a great chance to connect face-to-face and learn more. While our application window technically closes May 11, we’re using NY Tech Week to make space for a few last conversations before finalizing the next cohort.

title: Fintech x AI: Shaping the Future of Finance
description: Join us for Fintech x AI: Shaping the Future of Finance, a New York City Tech Week panel and reception hosted by HSBC Innovation Banking, a16z, and Fenwick. This exclusive reception will bring together leading VCs, founders, and senior executives for conversation and networking alongside a panel discussion on the current state of Fintech and AI, with David Haber, GP at a16z; Dylan Parker, CEO at Moment; and Andrew Wang, CEO at Valon, moderated by Dan Allred, Managing Director at HSBC US.

title: AI Meets Culture
description: AI Meets Culture: What’s Next for Consumer & Entertainment? A year after their memorable NY Tech Week 2024 discussion, Andrew Chen (General Partner, a16z) and Ian Goldstein (Startup & Venture Partner, Fenwick) reunite to explore how AI continues to reshape the consumer and entertainment landscape—this time joined by Gaurav Misra, CEO of Captions. From creator tools and social content to digital storytelling and cultural trends, the conversation will unpack how AI applications have evolved over the past year—and where they're headed next. Expect sharp insights, candid takes, and real-world perspectives from the frontlines of tech, venture, and entrepreneurship.
